        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 — \"A word was heard / And fertile ground / Was gladly found\"\nA cinematic still of an ancient Greco-Roman synagogue interior, shafts of dusty light from high windows illuminating a mixed crowd of Jews and Gentiles leaning in, listening intently to an unseen speaker. The mood is hopeful and receptive. Palette: warm amber and ochre, with deep shadows. Shot on 35mm film, natural light, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus — \"But rebels stirred the dust / They poisoned minds with deep mistrust\"\nA dramatic chiaroscuro shot. In the foreground, a shadowy figure in ancient Jewish attire whispers into the ear of a Roman-looking man, whose face shifts from curiosity to suspicion and anger. The background is a blurred, chaotic marketplace. Palette: high-contrast sepia, ember-and-shadow. Anamorphic lens, photorealistic.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 — \"The whisper starts / To break the hearts / The lie takes hold\"\nA close-up, symbolic image. A single drop of black ink falls into a crystal-clear glass of water, the dark tendrils slowly spreading and corrupting the whole glass. The lighting is stark and clinical, focusing entirely on the act of poisoning. Palette: monochrome with a hint of sepia. Macro lens, ultra-high resolution.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge — \"Their poisoned words will fade / Your word will stand, unafraid\"\nA symbolic landscape. In the foreground, withered, thorny vines lie on cracked, dry earth. In the background, a single, massive, ancient olive tree stands strong and vibrant under a clearing sky, with golden light breaking through dark, retreating storm clouds. Palette: sepia and dust in the foreground, transitioning to gold and deep blue in the background. Cinematic still, wide-angle lens.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro — \"They stir the dust / We hold the trust\"\nA close-up on two pairs of hands. One pair is angrily throwing dust into the air. The other pair is held together, firmly but gently cupping a small, simple clay oil lamp with a steady, burning flame that the dust cannot extinguish. Palette: warm, earthy tones, focused light on the lamp. Photorealistic, shallow depth of field.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: Title — \"Poisoned Minds\"\nAn ultra-high-resolution cinematic still capturing the core conflict. A man's face, half in shadow, half in light. On the shadow side, a whispering mouth is close to his ear, and his expression is one of growing anger and mistrust. On the light side, his expression is one of thoughtful consideration, looking toward an unseen source of light. The image is a visual representation of a soul being pulled in two directions by truth and slander. Palette: high-contrast chiaroscuro, sepia parchment tones.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The ultimate victory over the accuser.\nA symbolic, majestic scene. A powerful, unblemished Lamb stands atop a mountain, radiating pure, white light. Below, in a dark valley filled with shadow and mist, the indistinct form of a great dragon or serpent recoils from the light, its power broken. The image evokes Revelation 12 and 20, showing the final triumph of the Lamb over the accuser. Palette: brilliant gold and white against deep indigo and black. Volumetric light, cinematic still.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no face of Christ.\n```\n",
