ded, imminent violence. Sepia parchment, dust-light, and deep ochre shadows. Photorealistic, shot on 35mm film.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: The Christo-telic Horizon — the Cross as the ultimate \"stoning.\"\nSymbolic and cinematic still. A rough, empty wooden cross stands on a dark, rocky hill. At its base lies a single, blood-stained stone. The sky behind it is bruised and dark, but a single, powerful beam of golden light breaks through the clouds to illuminate the cross. This is the ultimate rejection, turned into the ultimate victory. High-contrast chiaroscuro, shot with an anamorphic lens.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no depiction of Christ's body.\n```",
