onsistency: Phase G Personal-Doing imperative, Memory Anchor Card APPLICATION line, Devotional Summary Take-away, and Retention Quiz Q4 all name the same actor and the same concrete act. PASS — All point to seeing setbacks as new mission fields.\n</code></pre>",
        "slide_deck_sidecar": "## Slide Deck Sidecar\n```markdown\n---\nbook: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"7\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre\n---\n\n# Acts 14:7 — Gospel Persistence Amidst Persecution\nThis single, powerful verse encapsulates the resilient, unstoppable nature of the Church's mission. After fleeing a murder plot, the apostles' immediate and continuous action was to keep preaching the gospel in the new territory God had sovereignly placed them in.\n\n*Slide deck: 7 sections, 7 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.*\n",
        "slide_deck_sidecar_html": "<h2>Slide Deck Sidecar</h2>\n<h2>```markdown</h2>\n<p>book: \"Acts\"\nchapter: \"14\"\nsection: \"7\"\nvisual_palette: sepia parchment, dust-light, ochre</p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Acts 14:7 — Gospel Persistence Amidst Persecution</h1>\n<p>This single, powerful verse encapsulates the resilient, unstoppable nature of the Church's mission. After fleeing a murder plot, the apostles' immediate and continuous action was to keep preaching the gospel in the new territory God had sovereignly placed them in.</p>\n<p><em>Slide deck: 7 sections, 7 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.</em></p>",
