 immediate leap to identifying Barnabas as Zeus and Paul as Hermes. All three streams converge on the central point: the Lystrans, operating from a pagan script, fundamentally misunderstood the miracle they witnessed.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Christ-Centered Hermeneutic Verification</strong>: This passage points to Christ by dramatic contrast. The crowd's cry, \"The gods have come down to us in the likeness of men!\" is precisely what happened in Jesus Christ, but in reality, not myth; for salvation, not capricious adventure. The Lystran error serves to magnify the glory, uniqueness, and truth of the Incarnation (Phil 2:6-8).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
